=== 密码学 ===

== 其他例子 ==
编码的其他例子包括：
* Encoding (in [[認知|認知]]) is a basic perceptual process of interpreting incoming stimuli; technically speaking, it is a complex, multi-stage process of converting relatively objective sensory input (e.g., light, sound) into subjectively meaningful experience.
* A [[content_format|content format]] is a specific encoding format for converting a specific type of [[数据|数据]] to [[信息|信息]].
* Text encoding uses a [[置标语言|置标语言]] to tag the structure and other features of a text to facilitate processing by computers. (See also Text Encoding Initiative.)
* {{tsl|en|Semantics encoding|语义编码}} of formal language A in formal language B is a method of representing all terms (e.g. programs or descriptions) of language A using language B.
* {{tsl|en|Encoder|编码器|电子编码}}，将信号转换为针对[[传输|传输]]或存储优化的代码，通常使用编解码器完成。 transforms a signal into a code optimized for [[传输|传输]] or [[儲存裝置|存储]], generally done with a [[编解码器|编解码器]].
* [[神经编码|神经编码]] is the way in which information is represented in [[神經元|neurons]].
* {{tsl|en|Encoding (memory)|记忆编码}}，将感觉转化为记忆的过程。
* [[類比電視|电视编码]]：[[NTSC制式|NTSC]], [[PAL制式|PAL]] and [[SECAM制式|SECAM]]
解码的其他例子包括：
* [[語法分析器|解码 (计算机科学)]]
* [[译码方法|译码方法]], methods in communication theory for decoding code words sent over a noisy channel
* [[数字信号处理|数字信号处理]], the study of signals in a digital representation and the processing methods of these signals
* [[數位類比轉換器|數位類比轉換器]], the use of analog circuit for decoding operations
* 单词[[基础语音教学法|解码]]，使用[[基础语音教学法|拼音]]将其译码为印刷图案，将它们译为语言读音

== 代码与首字母缩略词 ==
[[首字母縮略字|首字母縮略字]]和缩写可以认为是一种代码，并且某种意义上所有[[語言|語言]]和书写系统都是人类思维的代码。
